===Etymology 2===
From {{ME.}} '''[[beren]]''' meaning ''carry'' and ''bring forth''. The {{OE.}} root '''[[beran]]''' is related to Old High German '''[[beran]]''' meaning ''carry'', Gothic '''[[𐌱𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌰𐌽]]''' (''baíran''), Latin '''[[ferre]]''', and Greek '''[[φέρειν]]''' (''pherein''). These derive from the {{proto|Indo-European|bʰer-}}.

